d Borges—are eminent representatives of one and the other form, and all of the works analyzed are cases of a complex interplay between narrative and essay.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aFictionxHistory and criticism. 0aSkepticism in literature. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 4aLiterature : Narrative. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Critical Theory. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Comparative Literature.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2022z978311149185140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848681940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438486819423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438486819/original  a978-3-11-149185-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles